    Ecosystem

    Connect your smart contract to

    <Analytics; Machine Learning; Automation; Big Data; Computation; Deep Learning>

    On-chain computational agents (Cnidaria), Deeplink Cluster, and On-chain Neural Networks (ONN) enable greater programmability, automation, and analytics for smart contracts. The off-chain data & computation will be provided by Network Validators & off-chain Computation Providers. All on-chain and off-chain communication will go through the Deeplink L2 network & bridge to ensure security, and trustless, scalable operations. The deeplink developer toolkit will allow developers and data scientists to

    build, train and deploy data models, algorithms, and ML models for smart contracts.

     Deep Q-learning for on-chain execution test (DeepBrew: v1) is LIVE! 

    "Blockchain ecosystems will be unable to keep up with the ever-changing demands of needs, meet greater efficiencies and reduce vulnerabilities without an advanced level of automation and the emergence of intelligence".

    Collaborators

    Deeplink Techstack

    Deeplink makes blockchains smarter while maintaining decentralization and security.

    On-Chain Clusters are a group of smart contracts designed to facilitate and automate processes and run analytics and queries. They introduce intelligence to smart contracts, enabling On-Chain Computational Agents (Cnidaria) and On-Chain Neural Networks (ONN). On-Chain Clusters analyze and interpret patterns and structures in on-chain and off-chain data to enable learning, reasoning, and decision-making. Web3 developers and protocols can advance their ecosystemsDeFi, Blockchain Games, and Metaverses by leveraging On-Chain Clusters and On-Chain Computational agents to automate tasks, request data-driven recommendations and optimization, run analytics, predictions, and queries without compromising security and smart contract composability. The protocol provisions off-chain data and computation nodes to run selected On-Chain Clusters suggested and vetted by the community.
